Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring @butter{1%tbsp} to room temperature.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, ¾ tsp @garlic powder{1/4%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Rub all over with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Place on one side of a #baking sheet{}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 1 1/2 tsp garlic powder.

Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add the biscuits then).

Once chicken has roasted 5 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven.

Open tube of @Pillsbury™ Buttermilk Southern Homestyle Biscuits{1%6oz can}. Separate biscuits and carefully place on empty side of same #baking sheet{}.

Bake on top rack until biscuits are golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-11%minutes} more (chicken will finish cooking in the next step).

Once biscuits are golden brown, remove from oven and brush tops with softened butter. Sprinkle with remaining @garlic powder{3/4%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Top with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}.

Return to oven until chicken is cooked through and cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Pierce @green beans{6%ounce} bag with a fork; place bag on a #plate{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}.

Divide chicken, green beans, and biscuits between plates. Drizzle chicken with @honey{2%tsp} and serve.

> TIP: No microwave? No problem! Steam green beans in a small pot with a splash of water until just tender, 5-7 minutes. If you like, you can toss the green beans in a bowl with 1 TBSP butter for extra richness.